    narr:narration """This hub gathers the project's controlled vocabulary — the terms AsWritten/a collaborator insists on and the stylizations it holds canonical. The brand spine is [IP-as-code](narr:StyleObs_IPAsCode) (repeated 15+ times), [narrative architecture](narr:StyleObs_KeyPhrase_NarrArch), and [collective memory](narr:StyleObs_CollectiveMemoryTerm), with an explicit [terminology-control rule](narr:StyleObs_TerminologyControl) favoring 'worldview' over 'context' and 'collective memory' over 'semantic memory'. A coined-metaphor layer carries the argument: [context squishing](narr:Observation_ContextSquishing) names the black-box auto-summary problem, [cultivation trap](narr:Observation_CultivationTrap) names lock-in, and the [git-native triad](narr:Observation_GitNativeTriad) compresses versionable/branchable/reviewable. A defined-term layer fixes domain abstractions — [Memory](narr:Obs_MemoryDefinition), [Transaction](narr:Obs_TransactionDefinition), [compiled target](narr:Observation_CompiledTarget) — alongside startup-exit framing like [package to fundable state](narr:StyleObs_PackageFundable) and [intentional memory](narr:Observation_IntentionalMemory). The span is recognition-vocabulary: brand terms, coined metaphors, technical definitions, and stage/positioning shorthand (PMF, SSoT).""" ;
